body_html: When you build aten, it generates a Declarations.yaml which is much closer to what you are describing (it also contains all the legacy functions that are not implemented in native_functions but are still part of the public API). Note that these formats are part of the internals of the build, so we do make backwards incompatible changes to them from time to time.

body: When you build aten, it generates a `Declarations.yaml` which is much closer to what you are describing (it also contains all the legacy functions that are not implemented in native_functions but are still part of the public API).  Note that these formats are part of the internals of the build, so we do make backwards incompatible changes to them from time to time.
